        <div class="faq-a">Brass jet restriction — the brass orifices that meter gas flow to each burner are partially blocked by LA hard water mineral deposits combined with cooking oil residue. Yellow flame tips are the first visible sign. Weekly jet cleaning is the recommended maintenance for LA-installed Lacanche ranges. We clean all brass jets on every service visit, regardless of whether jet blockage was the stated complaint.</div>
