        <div class="faq-q">My Lacanche oven knob spins freely — does it need replacement?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Almost certainly not. Porcelain enamel Lacanche knobs loosen at the metric set screw — the knob spins freely while the control shaft stays in position. This is a 5-minute fix with an M3 metric hex key. We see this frequently and regularly save owners from ordering replacement knobs (8–10 week Art Culinaire lead time) for what's a set screw tightening job.</div>
